1.00	Dave_Berry_(American_football)	Dave Berry (American football)	David J. Berry was a major football manager during the late 19th and early 20th centuries. He was the top promotor for the sport during that time period. He is credited with inventing the "all-star game concept" in 1898, and also helped to form one of the first organized football leagues in 1902.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/67/1897_Latrobe.jpg
